      "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let's get started!</strong></p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat and boil a kettle</p><p>Peel and chop the <strong>brown onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> into wedges and slice the <strong>cherry tomatoes</strong> in half</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>onion wedges </strong>and <strong>halved cherry tomatoes </strong>to the pan with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and<strong> </strong>cook for 2-3 min or until starting to soften</p>",
